FAQ - PLEASE READ! I am not going to respond to questions that are covered here!

Q. I am interested in your gun. Is it still available?
A. If you see this ad, most likely. The firearms are reserved for pickup on my web site, by making an appointment to buy. Someone could be doing it right now, and first person to reserve the firearm wins. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment on the site. If someone has made it just before you, I will notify you within a short time (usually, an hour), otherwise - see you shortly.

PLEASE DO NOT ASK WHETHER THE GUN IS STILL AVAILABLE! I WILL NOT RESPOND.

Q. How do I buy?
A. This is a dealer listing, NICS check, taxes, etc are all required. Please go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick up.

Q. I am interested in your gun. Call me @ xxx-xxx-xxxx
A. Excellent. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick it up.

Q. Are there any other fees, in addition to the price and taxes? NICS, background check, etc?
A. No.

Q. What is the tax rate?
A. 9.5%

Q. Where are you located?
A. Queen Anne neighborhood in Seattle.

Q. Can we meet in Burien on Monday morning?
A. No, FFL requirements are that the transfers happen at a licensed location. Also, the only times you can come over are the appointments that you can reserve on the site. No other time slots are available.

Q. I see you carry Savage rifles. Can you find me MKII FV-SR?
A. No. Please see here for what I can or cannot do: http://www.preciseshooter.com/NotInStock.aspx

Q. Do you take trades?
A. Sometimes. However:
a) firearms only,
b) they need to be our of current production (I can get new ones at wholesale prices), or you have to offer them to me at well below wholesale
c) I do not resell the trades, so they should fit my personal interests (which only include military as well as highly accurate, competition guns - no self defense guns like Glocks, M&Ps, XD*, and the like)
d) the exchange rate should be fair (see here for more: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/PriceGuide.aspx

Q. Is the price firm? Will you take XXX (70% of the asking price)?
A. The price is firm.

Q. Can you help me mount a scope/replace a trigger/fix a feeding problem?
A. Sorry, I do not do gunsmithing.

Q. Will you ship?
A. Yes - go to www.preciseshooter.com -> How to buy and read the section for buying outside Seattle area. Shipping would be $25.

title: For Sale:  M1A Super Match 1990 Glen Nelson built
postcontent: For your consideration; One of the few carefully built rifles from master armorer; the late Glen Nelson of Columbus, Georgia. It is in the serial number range of the "Golden Age" of this rifles history. Glen was commissioned to make the Super Match rifles for Springfield Armory for many years. He only used USGI parts, which are superior to the ones used in today’s M1As. I read about a Super Match (in a ransom rest) that put fourteen rounds in a quarter sized hole at 200 yards! That’s the accuracy potential of these heavier “Douglas” barrels. The stock is beautifully bedded, it has a very low round count, as you can see by the trigger assembly, and is a superior battle rifle, home defense rifle, and it's a pretty darn good hunting rifle as well. Linseed oiled stock for weather protection. Original cleaning kit in stock butt. It was a "safe queen" for many years. If you are looking for the best of these legendary .308 caliber rifles, this is one of them. I’m thinning out my gun collection. This rifle comes with one twenty round SA brand magazine, and the hard shell plastic case it came in

title: For Sale/Trade:  AK-74: Bulgarian kit on Nodak Spud receiver - UPDATES
location: NE Mpls / Menomonie, WI, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
This is a Bulgarian parts kit assembled onto a Nodak Spud receiver.  The parts kit came with the front half of the gun completely assembled with a US barrel, non chrome lined.  The front half was assembled and properly headspaced by Centerfire Systems.  I refinished the buttstock, but it could be redone with a finer sanding and red stain to match.  The foregrips are left as original.  The outside of the receiver was blued using several coats of Birchwood Casey perma blue.  Sights are good to hit a 1'x2' steel plate at 100 yards, but I have not shot any paper off a good rest to precisely sight in. 

THE BAD:  I built this with a screw kit rather than rivets, and many of the screws on the front trunion and trigger guard stripped and fell out from recoil.  I've tried replacing them but the same problem occurs.  Plain and simply, AKs MUST be built with rivets.   If you or someone you know has the tools to rivet this together, perfect.  
UPDATES: I put in a few household screws to go shooting last weekend, but all of them stripped out and are gone now.  The oak pistol grip in the picture is not included, this will come with an unfinished pine grip I made as a first attempt.  

922r compliance:
-US made barrel (1)
-tapco G2 trigger group (3)
-Nodak Spud receiver (1)
-one 30 rd tapco mag (3)
-US pistol grip (1)
For a total of 9 US parts, 7 foreign parts.  (Fully legal to run foreign mags in it.)

title: For Sale:  Flag the Scammers *Buyers Beware!*
postcontent:
If an ad doesn't not have a specified city and IS NOT a dealer listing, please flag it as a scam. Armslist has been littered with scammers from Mexico and Africa. If the ad is fora high end firearm, and is significantly below retail, flag it. If the "seller" is out of state and they posted in our state, they want you to send a check/money order/postal money order or if the details have been copied from an auction site, flag it. Heres an example scam ad:

http://www.armslist.com/posts/1940105/missouri-rifles-for-sale--bushmaster--223-m4a1-with-accessories-223
